1
00:00:02,928 --> 00:00:05,306
Barney is crazy if he thinks
this is gonna work.

2
00:00:04,263 --> 00:00:05,222
I think it's
gonna work.

3
00:00:05,306 --> 00:00:06,432
I hope it doesn't work.

4
00:00:06,515 --> 00:00:07,975
Shh. Here he comes.

5
00:00:11,687 --> 00:00:14,398
You there, what's your name?
Excuse me?

6
00:00:14,440 --> 00:00:16,567
Your name, woman,
what's your name?!

7
00:00:16,650 --> 00:00:18,110
Cindy.
I knew it.

8
00:00:18,193 --> 00:00:20,154
You're the Cindy,

9
00:00:20,237 --> 00:00:22,448
the one who can change
everything,

10
00:00:22,531 --> 00:00:25,117
or spell our inevitable doom.

11
00:00:25,159 --> 00:00:27,328
Now listen to me, Cindy.

12
00:00:27,411 --> 00:00:28,746
I am Barney Stinson,

13
00:00:28,787 --> 00:00:32,041
and I am on an urgent mission
from the future.

14
00:00:32,082 --> 00:00:33,250
The future?

15
00:00:33,292 --> 00:00:35,669
The future, and I can
prove it to you.

16
00:00:35,711 --> 00:00:37,921
In exactly four seconds,
the woman at that booth

17
00:00:38,005 --> 00:00:39,715
is going to slap that man.
(clears throat)

18
00:00:41,967 --> 00:00:44,136
Ow! What the hell?

19
00:00:44,219 --> 00:00:45,929
Wow.
In a few minutes,

20
00:00:46,013 --> 00:00:48,599
the young me from your time

21
00:00:48,641 --> 00:00:50,934
is going to come
through that door.

22
00:00:51,018 --> 00:00:52,478
Now, Cindy,

23
00:00:52,519 --> 00:00:57,483
I know this sounds insane,
but in order to save the planet,

24
00:00:57,566 --> 00:01:00,319
you need to sleep with him
tonight.

25
00:01:00,402 --> 00:01:01,445
What? I...

26
00:01:01,528 --> 00:01:04,281
Sleep with Barney Stinson
tonight,

27
00:01:04,365 --> 00:01:05,949
in whatever way he wants it,

28
00:01:06,033 --> 00:01:10,120
or he won't be able to find
the solution to global warming

29
00:01:10,162 --> 00:01:11,955
that saves the human race.

30
00:01:12,039 --> 00:01:13,165
What are you talking about?

31
00:01:13,248 --> 00:01:15,250
I have no time to explain.

32
00:01:15,292 --> 00:01:17,670
I have to get back
to the reality accelerator

33
00:01:17,711 --> 00:01:20,839
before the vortex closes.

34
00:01:20,881 --> 00:01:23,133
Only you can save us, Cindy.

35
00:01:23,217 --> 00:01:25,344
I must away!

36
00:01:25,386 --> 00:01:28,222
Okay, guys, the movers
are coming in 14 hours.

37
00:01:28,305 --> 00:01:30,891
We gotta get back upstairs
and finish packing.

38
00:01:30,975 --> 00:01:32,977
You guys still
aren't finished packing?

39
00:01:33,018 --> 00:01:34,353
How is this taking so long?

40
00:01:34,436 --> 00:01:36,188
Hey, all the great memories
of our 20s

41
00:01:36,271 --> 00:01:37,481
took place in that apartment.

42
00:01:37,564 --> 00:01:39,525
It's not like throwing
stuff in a box.

43
00:01:39,608 --> 00:01:40,526
You start to reminisce.

44
00:01:40,609 --> 00:01:41,944
Not me. The key?

45
00:01:41,986 --> 00:01:43,445
Throw stuff out and never
look back.

46
00:01:43,487 --> 00:01:45,906
I'm moving to Japan.
It took me a half hour to pack.

47
00:01:45,948 --> 00:01:48,409
A half hour?
Well, it would have taken
me 20 minutes,

48
00:01:48,450 --> 00:01:49,868
but a friend called me in tears.

49
00:01:49,910 --> 00:01:52,663
Moving is really
emotional, okay?

50
00:01:52,746 --> 00:01:53,706
It is.

51
00:01:53,747 --> 00:01:55,332
I mean, everything is changing.

52
00:01:55,416 --> 00:01:57,376
I'm gonna be living
in New Jersey with Stella,

53
00:01:57,418 --> 00:01:59,211
you guys will be in
your new place.

54
00:01:59,294 --> 00:02:01,463
You're starting a new job
in Tokyo.

55
00:02:01,547 --> 00:02:03,632
It's the end of an era.

56
00:02:03,716 --> 00:02:06,093
I think we should have a toast,
but not our usual crap.

57
00:02:06,176 --> 00:02:09,054
Hey, uh, Wendy,
your most expensive
bottle of scotch.

58
00:02:09,138 --> 00:02:13,267
That's 50-year-old
Glen McKenna, and it's $2,500.

59
00:02:13,350 --> 00:02:15,644
Excellent. A bottle of that
with beer chasers,

60
00:02:15,686 --> 00:02:17,479
and what do you think,
cancel the scotch?

61
00:02:17,521 --> 00:02:19,440
ALL:
Yeah.

62
00:02:21,358 --> 00:02:22,318
Vodka rocks.

63
00:02:22,401 --> 00:02:24,111
It's not gonna work.

64
00:02:24,153 --> 00:02:27,448
Oh, my God, you're...
Oh, my God!

65
00:02:28,615 --> 00:02:29,616
Can I buy you a drink?

66
00:02:31,285 --> 00:02:33,829
I suppose I have time
for one drink

67
00:02:33,912 --> 00:02:37,583
and 45 minutes to an hour
of some other activity,

68
00:02:37,666 --> 00:02:39,460
but after that,
I have to get back

69
00:02:39,543 --> 00:02:42,254
to a top-secret research project
I'm working on.

70
00:02:42,338 --> 00:02:44,173
Global warming?

71
00:02:44,214 --> 00:02:47,801
My God, how did you know that?

72
00:02:47,802 --> 00:02:50,102
